com.ibm.team.build.ant.task
Class GetNextBuildRequestTask

java.lang.Object
  Task
      com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.AbstractTeamBuildTask
          com.ibm.team.build.ant.task.GetNextBuildRequestTask

public final class GetNextBuildRequestTask
extends AbstractTeamBuildTask

Ant task to retrieve the next build request for a specified engine and optional build definition. The request id returned from this task should then be used in either one of two ways:

  1. Be passed to StartBuildTask to start a build for the request.
  2. Be passed to CompleteBuildTask setting the buildNotNecessary attribute to true. This 2nd case is generally only used when a requested build is retrieved but it's determined that there are no changes so a build is not necessary.

The build definition properties associated with the request are automatically defined as ant properties if a request for the specified engine is retrieved.

Required attributes are:

  • engineId - The id of the engine to retrieve the next build request for.
  • requestUUIDProperty - The ant property to store the UUID of the next build request for the specified engine. It will only be defined if a request for the specified engine is retrieved.

Optional attributes are:

  • requestUUIDFile - The path relative to the base directory of the build file or the full path to a file in which to store the uuid of the next build request for the specified build engine.. The file is formatted as a java.util.Properties format and contains a property with the name specified by requestUUIDProperty.
  • buildDefinitionId - If this attribute is specified, the request retrieved will be a request for a build with the given build definition id. If the build definition id is not supported by the specified build engine then a request will not be retrieved.
  • buildDefinitionIdProperty - The ant property to store build definition id of the next build request for the specified engine. It will only be defined if a request for the specified engine is retrieved. Note: This property does not apply when the buildDefinitionId is used.
See AbstractTeamBuildTask for additional required and optional attributes.

Since:
0.5
